Why Context Matters?
Context gives meaning. Without it, facts can mislead and opinions can be misunderstood. At A2D, we tackle complex and sometimes controversial tech, finance, business topics. I'm "The Indian Motovlogger", a vlogger from Delhi roaming the Indian terrain on two wheels. 
I have a drive for adventure and I love visiting new places. 
But what I enjoy the most is the ride to my destination. Riding is also my getaway solution. So join me on my rides, get away from your busy life to live the moment. 
Also, don't forget to like and comment on my videos.

All India Save Education Committee welcomes you to this channel. Since its inception the AISEC has stood for modern scientific, secular, democratic and universal education. Presently it stands gravely concerned with the promulgation and implementation of the National Education Policy 2020, which tends to shatter whatever vestiges of scientific secular education still exists in the country, paves smooth way for putting education totally in the grip of profit-hungry corporate houses and spells doom for academic autonomy and democratic rights of primary stakeholders of education. It pledges for reinventing past Indian glory through so-called Indian Knowledge System, as also imports failed systems from the USA. The AISEC calls upon education fraternity and common people as well, to join its All India Save Education Conference on 30 -31 October to further its efforts to build sustained organized movement against NEP 2020.

Description:
Welcome to ISLRTCтАЩs YouTube channel where you can learn about Indian Sign Language (ISL), the sign language used by the deaf community in India. 
ISLRTC is an autonomous body under the DEPwD, MSJ&E, Government of India. ISLRTC was established in 2015 to promote the use of ISL to make society accessible for deaf people. 
ISLRTCтАЩs YouTube channel contains different types of resources such as:
- ISL dictionary including everyday terms, legal terms, academic terms, etc. and recently launched financial terms
- Online self-learning course on basic ISL of 30-40 hours 
- Basic orientation with 200 signs for communication with 3-4 year old children
- NCERT textbooks in ISL
- Various important information and announcements by the government in ISL (eg. Har Ghar Tiranga, Azadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav, Cyber Jagrookta, anti-ragging campaign, etc.)

Description:
The main purpose of ISH News is to provide the news and information in accessible format to the 18 million deaf people in India. As the News Channels on TV convey the information in spoken language, the deaf people are deprived of such information since they cannot hear. Sign Language is the natural language of the deaf since, with their missing sense of hearing, the deaf rely heavily on the sense of sight and touch for communication in their daily lives. Hence, every video of ISH News narrated in Indian Sign Language will greatly benefit the deaf people with access to information.

The inclusion of closed-captions and background voice ensures that the News is also accessible to the public and promotes the inclusion of all individuals, whilst maintaining the awareness on deafness. With this тАЬinclusionтАЭ, our aim is to create equal opportunities for the people with disabilities.

Indian College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists (ICOG) is the academic wing of Federation of Obstetric and Gynaecological Societies of India (FOGSI), one of world largest professional organizations of medical practitioners.  ICOG was established on December 21, 1984 at Durgapur on the occasion of 28th All India Congress of Obstetrics and Gynaecology (AICOG).

In 2020, ICOG moved to the online platform for training and CME activities.

This year, we take it forward by introducing structured Online ICOG Weekend Courses in various disciplines like Ultrasound, Gynec Onco, Critical Care, Asthetic and Regenarative Gynecology to name a few.

Krishnan Nair Shantakumari Chithra (born 27 July 1963), is an Indian playback singer from Kerala. Chithra also sings Indian classical, devotional, and popular music. She has lent her voice to Malayalam, Kannada, Tamil, Telugu, Oriya, Hindi, Assamese, Bengali, Badaga, Sanskrit, Tulu, Urdu and Punjabi songs. Through a career spanning more than three decades, she has recorded over 20,000 songs. She is a recipient of six National Film Awards (the most by any female singer), five Filmfare Awards South and 31 different state film awards. She has won all the four south Indian state film awards. Chithra is popularly and fondly referred to as Chinna Kuyil (Little Nightingale of South India) or Keralathinte Vanambadi (Nightingale of Kerala).

Description:
You will find philosophy lectures in Hindi on this channel, with an easy and fun premise for all round understanding and grasp of the subject. The channel aims to cover anything & everything, under the philosophical umbrella (except religious preachings)

My goal is to empower the masses with the tools & frameworks of philosophy so that they can win in life both emotionally & financially.

I am not a qualified academic philosopher or do not possess any formal degree in the field of Philosophy. I love making difficult philosophical concepts easier to understand for the masses, I am a vessel for carrying the words of the long gone!

The term 'desi' in the channel name does not mean that I am required to create lectures on Indian philosophy. Instead, 'desi' signifies my approach to deciphering and teaching Western philosophy in the Hindi language. The channel is intended for individuals who may not be proficient in English but still have a strong interest in Western philosophy.
